The paper discusses the use of affective multimedia databases in research related to attention and emotion processing, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also introduces a new ontology for the description of affective multimedia stimuli, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the retrieval of multimedia stimuli, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on the description of multimedia stimuli, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
